node.text: It was a beautiful day and I’m in love with my new daughter-in-law. Check out this video shot and produced by Stephen Norregaard. See the full wide format version here: https://vimeo.com/308998543

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on September 19, 2021 tagging @stofferphotographyinteriors, @stofferhome, and @stofferhomecabinetry. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: “Butler’s Pantry” seems like an outdated title for a room  But this room at The Madison has design elements rescued from a bygone era. Beautiful cabinetry to store china and serve ware.  A German silver sink to wash all of it, and direct access to the dining room through a swinging door. The blue-gray color sets just the perfect mood. All that is why I wanted a wall of glass from the hallway to be able to see it. It’s just so pretty. @stofferhomecabinetry in Sutton Blue (some cabinetry is original to the house) Lighting from @stofferhome  Photog: @stofferphotographyinteriors

node.text: This is the bedroom at our old house, the #jsdenglishcottage  It is a testament to what can be done with a converted attached garage. Does this give anyone hope for their own house?  Check out my stories for before, during and after!  Bed, tree prints and pillows from @stofferhome

node.text: Old houses like The Madison can have such interesting nooks and crannies like the vestibule. Do you have an older home with a little spot that you love?  Tell me about it! node.text: Our #jsdenglishbrick project had a spectacular 1920’s original arched opening into the back porch. (Second slide). We converted that porch into a laundry room/mudroom. And we felt that arch must be repeated in the kitchen remodel so we widened the opening between the dining room and kitchen, and found the best place for the arch (first slide). Lighting and hardware from @stofferhome Cabinetry in Kensington Taupe and Bromley Taupe from @stofferhomecabinetry  Photography by @stofferphotographyinteriors

node.text: Check out the B & A of the main bathroom suite at The Madison. There were plenty of bedrooms in the 1902 house but only tiny closets and small bathrooms. We solved both problems by breaking through to a bedroom and capturing its space for the Main Suite. Threw in a drink fridge which is pretty great. I have tagged sources and don’t forget about our Labor Day Sale @stofferhome 20% off almost everything. 😍

node.text: Some people actually spend quite a bit of time in the powder room. 😬 So why not make it nice, right? #jsdenglishcottage  Mirror is antique. Sconces from @stofferhome My husband and I built the brass base with railing parts. You didn’t know I was a DIY’er did you??

node.text: One of my faves. The #jsd1902victorian is small and layered with architectural goodness. Cabinetry is in Kensington Taupe and Eastbourne from @stofferhomecabinetry Lighting, hardware and accessories from @stofferhome Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors .

node.text: It’s raining and I love it. We really need it and the clouds make our dining room at The Madison all dark and moody. Maybe we should light some candles and have dinner in there!  Paint color is Grizzle Gray from @sherwinwilliams

node.text: A little swipe action to see one the most simple and timeless kitchens we’ve done. The #jsdenglishcottage which was my old house before moving to The Madison. 😍 The cabinetry is in Kensington Taupe from @stofferhomecabinetry and you can find all the hardware and lighting @stofferhome Photographed with natural light only on an extremely gray January day by the talented duo @johnstoffer and @maurastoffer
